The paper discusses Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and their use in unsupervised representation learning. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Given the focus on deep Energy Based Models (EBMs) and feature extraction for classification, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories. However, the paper also touches on topics related to natural language processing and perceptual similarity, which could place it in the cs.CL and cs.NE categories as well.
